<br />Also.....the way 6809 works with the Y register is to add a $10 (IIRC) in front of a X register instruction. If the 65816 has 2 other opcodes unused, could you double the registers by just taking that and adding it in front of every instruction to reverse the registers used in the instruction to a extended register set to double the registers on the chip? I am understanding how this works, right? XD

		

